gurmukhi: AweI mnwvn hY hmko su khI bqIXw ju nhI ruceI hY ] kop kY au`qr dyq BeI cl rI cl qUM ikn bIc deI hY ]692]
transliteration: Ooimanaavan Hai Houmko Su Kahibateeyaa Ju Nahirouchaihai|| Kop Kai Outtar Det Bhaichal Richal Toon Beech Daihai||692||
translation: “You have come to persuade me, but whatever you have talked, I have not liked;” in great ire, Radha said, “You go away from this place and do not meddle in between us uselessly.”692.
Speech of the messenger addressed to Krishna:

gurmukhi: kop kY au`qr dyq BeI ien Awie kihXo iPir sMg sujwnY ] bYT rhI hT mwn qRIXw hau mnwie rhI jV ikauhU n mwnY ]
transliteration: Kop Kai Outtar Det Bhaiin Aae Kahiyo Phir(i) San Sujaanai|| Baith Rahihath Maan Treeyaa Hau Manaae Rahijad Kiohoo Na Maanai||
translation: The messenger said to Krishna in ire that Radha was giving her replies in anger; she seems determined on her female persistence and she with her idiotic intellect is not agreeing in any way;

gurmukhi: swm dIey n mnY nhI dMf mnY nhI Byd jIey Aru dwnY ] AYsI guvwr so hyq khw qumrI joaU pRIq ko rMg n jwnY ]693]
transliteration: Saam Deee Na Manai Nahidand Manai Nahibhed Jeee Ar(u) Dnai|| Aisiguvr So Het Kah Toumrijooo Preet Ko Ran Na Aanaee||693||
translation: She has not agreed in any of the four: calmness, restraint, penalty and difference; she is also not comprehending the facet of your love; what is the use of loving such an uncivilised gopi? 693.

gurmukhi: mYn pRBw bwc kwnH jU so ]
translation: Speech of Mainprabha addressed to Krishna:

gurmukhi: mYn pRBw hir pws huqI sun kY bqIXw qb bol auTI hY ] ilAwieho hau ieh BwNq kihXo qum qy hir jU joaU gÍwr ruTI hY ]
transliteration: Main-prabhaa Har(i) Paas Houtisoun Kai Bateeaa Tab Bol Outhihai|| Liaaeho Hau Eh Bhaant Kahiyo Toum Te Har(i) Joo Jooo Gvaar Routhihai||
translation: A gopi named Mainprabha, who was standing near Krishna, listening to the messenger, said, “O Krishna ! the gopi who was become angry with you, I shall bring her.”

gurmukhi: kwnH ky pwien pY qbhI su ilXwvn qwhI ky kwj auTI hY ] suMdrqw muK aUpr qy mno kMj pRBw sB vwr sutI hY ]694]
transliteration: Kaahn Ke Paain Pai Tab-hisu Liyaavan Taahike Kaaj Outhihai|| Soundartaa Moukh Oopar Te Mano Kanj Prabhaa Sabh Vaar Soutihai||694||
translation: In order to bring her to Krishna, that gopi got up; seeing her beauty, it seems that the lotus has sacrificed all its beauty on her.694.

gurmukhi: hir pwien pY ieh BwNq khXo hirjU auhky iFg hau cil jYho ] jwhI aupwv qy Awie hY suMdir qwhI aupwie mnwie ilXY ho ]
transliteration: Har(i) Paain Pai Eh Bhaant Kahyo Har(i)jjoo Uhke Dhig Hau Chal(i) Jaiho|| Jaahioupaav Te Aae Hai Soundar(i) Taahioupaae Manaae Liyai Ho||
translation: Standing near Krishna, Mainprabha said, “I shall go myself to her and with whatever means she comes, I shall persuade and bring her;

gurmukhi: pwien pY ibnqIAn kY irJvwiekY suMdr gÍwr mnYho ] AwjhI qo iFg Awn imlYho jU lXwie ibnw qumrI n khY ho ]695]
transliteration: Paaeen Pai Bineen Kai Rijhvaae-kai Rijvaae-kai Binteean Kai Rijhaae-kai Soundar Gvaar Manaiho|| At In To Dheeg Aan Milaiho Joo Layaae Bibnaa Toumrina Kahai Ho||695||
translation: “I shall get the assent of that winsome gopi, either by falling at her feet, or by request or getting her pleased; I shall bring her to you even today, otherwise I shall not be called yours.”695.

gurmukhi: hir pwien pY iqh Taur clI kib sXwm khY Pun mYn pRBw ] ijh ky lgI qu`il mdodr hY ijh qu`il qRIXw nih ieMdR sBw ]
transliteration: Har(i) Paaeen Pai Tih Tharu Chalikabi Syaam Kahai Phoun Main-prabhaa|| Ji Ke Lakh Tull(i) Madodar Hai Jih Tull(i) Treeyaa Nah(i) Indra Sabhaa||
translation: Getting up from near Krishna, Mainprabha started; Mandodari does not equal her in beauty and none the damsels of the court of Indra, has any charm before her;

gurmukhi: ijh ko muK suMdr rwjq hY ieh BwNq lsY qRIXw vwkI ABw ] mno cMd kurMgn kyhr kIr pRBw ko sBo Dn Xwih lBw ]696]
transliteration: Jih Ko Moukh Soundar Raajat Hai Eh Bhaant Lasiai Treeyaa Vaakiabhaa|| Mano Channd Kuranad Kaehar Keer Prabhaa Ko Sabho Dhan Yaah(i) Labhaa||696||
translation: The glory of this woman’s charming face appears like this that the moon, deer, lion and parrot have borrowed their wealth of beauty from her.696.
